            <title>[DERBY-485] SecurityException or LinkageException thrown during loading a class from a database jar incorrectly shuts the engine down.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-485</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In addiing test cases to lang/dcl.test for signed jar files stored in the database I found that if a jar is installed with a tampered class the resulting SecurityException shuts Derby down. Most likely the same would be true for an invalid class hacked into the jar.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
